          "type": "link"
        }
      ],
      "name": "Dezullon Thicket",
      "sources": [
        {
          "link": {
            "alt": "Battlecry! pg. 177",
            "aonid": 268,
            "game-obj": "Sources",
            "name": "Battlecry! pg. 177",
            "type": "link"
          },
          "name": "Battlecry!",
          "page": 177,
          "type": "source"
        }
      ],
      "text": "It is thankfully uncommon to encounter more than one dezullon within a few square miles, largely because few ecosystems contain enough prey to sustain more than one of the ravenous flesh-eating plants for long. When a well-fed dezullon finds a suitably abundant location, however, it occasionally takes root, blooms, and shortly thereafter expels dozens of fist-sized seed pods. Should enough of the resulting saplings survive to full size, they temporarily merge into a tangled mass of grasping tendrils and sweep across the area, voraciously scouring their environment clean of any remaining game before dispersing to seek their own hunting grounds.",
      "type": "section"
    }
  ],
  "sources": [
